{{2020 ACC football standings}}

The '''2020 Atlantic Coast Conference football season''', part of the [[2020 NCAA Division I FBS football season]], was the 68th season of [[college football]] play for the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] (ACC). It began on September 3, 2020, and ended in January 2021. For 2020, the ACC consisted of 15 members in one division.<ref name="postpone">{{cite web|url=https://theacc.com/news/2020/7/29/general-acc-announces-plans-for-football-and-fall-olympic-sports.aspx|title=ACC Announces Plans for Football and Fall Olympic Sports|website=theacc.com|publisher=The Atlantic Coast Conference|date=July 29, 2020|access-date=July 30, 2020}}</ref>

The original 2020 schedule was released on January 22, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theacc.com/news/2020/1/21/acc-announces-2020-football-schedule.aspx|title=2020 ACC Football Schedule Released|website=ACC Sports.com|date=January 22, 2020|access-date=January 22, 2020}}</ref>  On July 29, a revised concept of the schedule was released in the wake of the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United States|COVID-19 pandemic]].  It was announced that teams would play a ten-game conference schedule, which would include [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish football|Notre Dame]].  An option was left for one out-of-conference game, provided that game was played in the home state of the ACC school.<ref name="postpone"/>

==Preseason==

===ACC Kickoff===

Due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United States|COVID-19 pandemic]], the ACC announced that its 2020 Football Kickoff would be held virtually instead of at the Westin in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]].  The Kickoff was scheduled for July 21–23, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theacc.com/news/2020/6/17/2020-acc-football-kickoff-to-be-conducted-virtually.aspx|title=2020 ACC Football Kickoff to be Conducted Virtually|website=theacc.com|publisher=The Atlantic Coast Conference|date=June 18, 2020|access-date=June 24, 2020}}</ref>  On July 13, it was announced that the Kickoff was postponed until further notice.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theacc.com/news/2020/7/13/football-acc-virtual-kickoff-postponed.aspx|title=Virtual ACC Football Kickoff Postponed|website=theacc.com|publisher=The Atlantic Coast Conference|date=July 13, 2020|access-date=July 17, 2020}}</ref>  On September 4, 2020, the ACC Preseason Media Poll was released.<ref name="pre">{{cite web|url=https://theacc.com/news/2020/9/4/clemson-leads-2020-acc-preseason-football-selections.aspx|title=Clemson Leads 2020 ACC Preseason Football Selections|website=theacc.com|publisher=The Atlantic Coast Conference|date=September 4, 2020|access-date=September 14, 2020}}</ref>

