==Coaches==

=== Coaching changes ===
The ACC entered the 2020 season with two new head football coaches:

* On November 4, 2019, Florida State head coach [[Willie Taggart]] was fired<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/ncaaf/2019/11/03/fsu-football-willie-taggart-fired-second-season/4150435002/|title=Florida State football fires head coach Willie Taggart during second season|work=USA Today|date=November 3, 2019|access-date=January 22, 2020}}</ref> and replaced by [[Mike Norvell]] on December 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/28246814/mike-norvell-hired-florida-state-new-coach|title=Mike Norvell hired as Florida State's new coach|first=Adam|last=Rittenberg|access-date=December 26, 2018}}</ref>
* On December 1, 2019, Boston College head coach [[Steve Addazio]] was fired after seven seasons and a  starting the season 2–8.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/college/bostoncollege/football/steve-addazio-fired-by-boston-college|title=Report: Head Coach Steve Addazio Fired After Seven Years At Boston College|website=Sports Illustrated|first=A.J.|last=Black|date=December 1, 2019|access-date=January 15, 2020}}</ref> [[Jeff Hafley]] was named head coach on December 14, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Boston College Names Jeff Hafley Head Football Coach |url=https://bceagles.com/news/2019/12/14/boston-college-names-jeff-hafley-head-football-coach.aspx |language=en}}</ref>

